==English==
{{wikipedia}}

[[Image:Ceres_statue.jpg|240px|[[Ceres]], the [[Roman empire|Roman]] goddess of [[agriculture]]|right]]

===Etymology===
From Middle English < Old English, modelled on other masculine>feminine nouns, after the gender of the neuter word ''god'' was shifted to masculine by Christianity.  See [[God]] for further etymology.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: gŏd'ĕs
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈgɒdes/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"gQdes/

===Proper noun===
'''Goddess'''

# The single goddess of various [[monotheistic]] religions.
# The single female god of various [[ditheistic]] religions. <!-- eg Wicca -->
# An impersonal and universal spiritual presence or force.
# An omnipotent being, creator of the universe.

